<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>pavement artist <i>(UK)</i> • pavement artist <i>(U.S.)</i></xh5><p> <i>pavement artist (UK)—</i>1. <i>(also: flagstone artist)</i> an artist who draws on paving stones with colored chalks, hoping to be given money by passers-by: No one but the <u>pavement artist</u> can have any notion of how great the amount of dust is in London’s streets. 2. <i>(sl.)</i> an espionage agent engaged in street surveillance on a suspect, etc.: His specialty was hitting the streets and finding out information. In the vernacular of his profession he became known as a top-notch “<u>pavement artist</u>.” </p><p><i>pavement artist (U.S.)—</i>an artist who displays paintings for sale on a pavement: Outside the station a small crowd were watching with interest as a <u>pavement artist</u> copied and enlarged a painting from a postcard.</p> </entry>
